</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,522,652]" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">
Siphons 25–40 µm diameter; branches frequent.Alga monoecious; antheridia lateral to 1–2 oogonia borne on a gametophore; gametophores frequent (
<figureCitation box="[283,342,558,580]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="15.[136,229,1360,1382]" captionTargetBox="[346,1241,167,1346]" captionTargetId="figure-18@15.[346,1241,167,1346]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 8. Light micrographs and illustrations of Vaucheria edaphica reproductive structures (UCVT1).A, C, G, I. Gametophore bearing pendent, mostly sessile oogonia with distal prominence and a circinate antheridium, note oospores covering entire portion of oogonium. B, D. Single reniform oogonium with circinate antheridium. E, F. Developing oogonia; note green colouration. J, K, L. Variations of gametophore arrangement. Scale bars = 20 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147012" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147012/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Antheridia circinate, 70–90 µm long × 20–35 µm diameter. Oogonia 1–2, reniform, pendent, 75–100 µm long × 25–35 µm diameter, mostly sessile, rarely with short pedicels (always &lt;10 µm long); distal prominence towards peduncle; wall thin. Oospores same size as oogonia, no oogonial cavity left behind by mature oospores.
</paragraph>
